 & =\frac{1}{y}\frac{1}{\sqrt{2\pi}\sigma}\exp\left(-\frac{1}{2\sigma^{2}}\left(\ln y-\mu-\ln a\right)^{2}\right)
\end{align*}

\end_inset

which means that 
\begin_inset Formula $Y\sim LogN(\mu+\ln a,\sigma^{2})$
\end_inset

.
